=\"ab ac ae af ag dq ai aj\"><p id=\"5414\" class=\"hk hl dt hm b hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih dl eq\">Self-help books often get a bad rap for being cheesy and out-of-touch. But, it’s undeniable that personal reflection and growth are critical elements of living a happy and fulfilled life. So what should you read that might truly change the way you think about, experience, and behave in your life?</p><p id=\"beb4\" class=\"hk hl dt hm b hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih dl eq\">Below, you’ll find 9 of our favorite personal development books. Each author on this list has a very unique voice, but all of them have one thing in common: they are great at “real talk.” You won’t find a lot of bullshit advice among these pages, which is why we love them. Give one—or all—of them a read. They just might change your life.</p></div></div></section><div class=\"n p er ii ij ik\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in\"></span></div><section class=\"dl dm dn do dp\"><div class=\"n p\"><div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dq ai aj\"><figure class=\"gs gt gu gv gw gr cx cy paragraph-image\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/the-subtle-art-of-not-giving-a-f-ck\"><div class=\"cx cy ip\"><div class=\"hc s hd he\"><div class=\"iq hg s\"><div class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj bk ha hb\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj hh hi hj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/42/1*OMfwgSz4AZnOEnTlymKJRg.png?q=20\" width=\"288\" height=\"412\" role=\"presentation\"/></div><img alt=\"\" class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj c\" width=\"288\" height=\"412\" role=\"presentation\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*OMfwgSz4AZnOEnTlymKJRg.png\" width=\"288\" height=\"412\" srcSet=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*OMfwgSz4AZnOEnTlymKJRg.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*OMfwgSz4AZnOEnTlymKJRg.png 288w\" sizes=\"288px\" role=\"presentation\"/></noscript></div></div></div></a></figure><p id=\"5e33\" class=\"hk hl dt hm b hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih dl eq\">If you’ve read any of popular blog writer <a href=\"https://markmanson.net/\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">Mark Manson</strong></a><strong class=\"hm is\">’s</strong> content, you know you’re in for a treat with this one. <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/the-subtle-art-of-not-giving-a-f-ck\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">The Subtle Art of Not Giving a F*ck</strong></a> is a truly refreshing take on what it means to live a great life. Manson is a tell-it-like-it-is guy, dropping lines like, “In life, we have a limited amount of fucks to give. So you must choose your fucks wisely.” Still, his writing is genuine and hits you right in the gut—in the best possible way. If you can’t stand traditional self-help books but are still curious about what it means to live a life full of happiness and contentment (who doesn’t?), this is the perfect book for you.</p></div></div></section><div class=\"n p er ii ij ik\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in\"></span></div><section class=\"dl dm dn do dp\"><div class=\"n p\"><div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dq ai aj\"><figure class=\"gs gt gu gv gw gr cx cy paragraph-image\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/if-you-feel-too-much\"><div class=\"cx cy ip\"><div class=\"hc s hd he\"><div class=\"it hg s\"><div class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj bk ha hb\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj hh hi hj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/46/1*S6ME3kyP_LwRuVGb8kJrfw.png?q=20\" width=\"288\" height=\"368\" role=\"presentation\"/></div><img alt=\"\" class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj c\" width=\"288\" height=\"368\" role=\"presentation\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*S6ME3kyP_LwRuVGb8kJrfw.png\" width=\"288\" height=\"368\" srcSet=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*S6ME3kyP_LwRuVGb8kJrfw.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*S6ME3kyP_LwRuVGb8kJrfw.png 288w\" sizes=\"288px\" role=\"presentation\"/></noscript></div></div></div></a></figure><p id=\"57f8\" class=\"hk hl dt hm b hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih dl eq\">This is a breathtakingly written <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/if-you-feel-too-much\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">memoir</strong></a> from the founder of <a href=\"https://twloha.com/\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">To Write Love On Her Arms</strong></a><strong class=\"hm is\">, </strong>a non-profit aimed at presenting hope for people who struggle with addiction, depression, self-injury, and thoughts of suicide. Author Jamie Tworkowski touches on achey subjects—from heartbreak to the death of loved ones. This is a soothing, and ultimately a redemptive, read that will make you feel like you’ve got a friend who knows exactly what you were going through during the toughest experiences of your own life.</p></div></div></section><div class=\"n p er ii ij ik\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in\"></span></div><section class=\"dl dm dn do dp\"><div class=\"n p\"><div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dq ai aj\"><figure class=\"gs gt gu gv gw gr cx cy paragraph-image\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/daring-greatly\"><div class=\"cx cy ip\"><div class=\"hc s hd he\"><div class=\"iu hg s\"><div class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj bk ha hb\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj hh hi hj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/40/1*Fmw2pQYw-YV2ZIEI-cWjVA.png?q=20\" width=\"288\" height=\"435\" role=\"presentation\"/></div><img alt=\"\" class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj c\" width=\"288\" height=\"435\" role=\"presentation\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*Fmw2pQYw-YV2ZIEI-cWjVA.png\" width=\"288\" height=\"435\" srcSet=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*Fmw2pQYw-YV2ZIEI-cWjVA.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*Fmw2pQYw-YV2ZIEI-cWjVA.png 288w\" sizes=\"288px\" role=\"presentation\"/></noscript></div></div></div></a></figure><p id=\"3d12\" class=\"hk hl dt hm b hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih dl eq\">It has to be said: <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/daring-greatly\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">Daring Greatly</strong></a> is one of those books that every human on the planet should read. If everyone understood and lived by the concepts that author Brené Brown explores, we’d all be happier and better for it. This book centers around the topic of vulnerability, exploring what it means to live a courageous life in a world where we too often make decisions out of fear that we’ll get hurt or be criticized. This is a powerful book that will change your willingness and practice around letting yourself be fully seen—by loved ones and strangers alike.</p></div></div></section><div class=\"n p er ii ij ik\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in\"></span></div><section class=\"dl dm dn do dp\"><div class=\"n p\"><div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dq ai aj\"><figure class=\"gs gt gu gv gw gr cx cy paragraph-image\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/tiny-beautiful-things\"><div class=\"cx cy ip\"><div class=\"hc s hd he\"><div class=\"iv hg s\"><div class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj bk ha hb\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj hh hi hj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/40/1*sw42Rk9IkrBVZTEC1XlEMQ.png?q=20\" width=\"288\" height=\"443\" role=\"presentation\"/></div><img alt=\"\" class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj c\" width=\"288\" height=\"443\" role=\"presentation\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*sw42Rk9IkrBVZTEC1XlEMQ.png\" width=\"288\" height=\"443\" srcSet=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*sw42Rk9IkrBVZTEC1XlEMQ.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*sw42Rk9IkrBVZTEC1XlEMQ.png 288w\" sizes=\"288px\" role=\"presentation\"/></noscript></div></div></div></a></figure><p id=\"3591\" class=\"hk hl dt hm b hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih dl eq\">This is legitimately one of the most beautifully self-help books you’ll ever read. Author Cheryl Strayed compiles a series of Q&amp;As from her days as an anonymous advice columnist—and boy, will her thoughts blow you away. <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/tiny-beautiful-things\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">Tiny Beautiful Things</strong></a> takes readers on a journey through seemingly impossible topics like: navigating divorce, unrequited love, addiction, betrayal, and forgiveness. Her advice feels deeply genuine and honest‚ like you’re getting it from a much smarter, more compassionate big sister. Author Ryan Holiday says, “This book contains some of the most cogent insights on life, pain, loss, love, success, and youth that I have ever seen.” He’s not exaggerating. Go read this one now.</p></div></div></section><div class=\"n p er ii ij ik\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in\"></span></div><section class=\"dl dm dn do dp\"><div class=\"n p\"><div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dq ai aj\"><figure class=\"gs gt gu gv gw gr cx cy paragraph-image\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/leadership-and-self-deception\"><div class=\"cx cy ip\"><div class=\"hc s hd he\"><div class=\"iv hg s\"><div class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj bk ha hb\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj hh hi hj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/40/1*NEzaoyUXVoPnnxyi7x5rKw.png?q=20\" width=\"288\" height=\"443\" role=\"presentation\"/></div><img alt=\"\" class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj c\" width=\"288\" height=\"443\" role=\"presentation\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*NEzaoyUXVoPnnxyi7x5rKw.png\" width=\"288\" height=\"443\" srcSet=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*NEzaoyUXVoPnnxyi7x5rKw.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*NEzaoyUXVoPnnxyi7x5rKw.png 288w\" sizes=\"288px\" role=\"presentation\"/></noscript></div></div></div></a></figure><p id=\"d3d2\" class=\"hk hl dt hm b hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih dl eq\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/leadership-and-self-deception\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">Leadership and Self-Deception</strong></a> is the kind of book that will completely change the quality of your relationships—at work and beyond—for the better. Through memorable storytelling, It reads almost like a novel, but it does an incredible job of getting readers to think about how we view others and why that impacts our ability to lead (or even communicate effectively) with them. You’ll walk away from this one with a renewed perspective on what it means to lead well by first changing your own thinking, along with strengthening your ability to relate to and empathize with others. You’ll never look at the critical conversations you have—at work or home—the same way again.</p></div></div></section><div class=\"n p er ii ij ik\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in\"></span></div><section class=\"dl dm dn do dp\"><div class=\"n p\"><div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dq ai aj\"><figure class=\"gs gt gu gv gw gr cx cy paragraph-image\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/mindset-2\"><div class=\"cx cy ip\"><div class=\"hc s hd he\"><div class=\"iw hg s\"><div class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj bk ha hb\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj hh hi hj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/38/1*urpfDN5v3xZ41XskIApfFA.png?q=20\" width=\"288\" height=\"448\" role=\"presentation\"/></div><img alt=\"\" class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj c\" width=\"288\" height=\"448\" role=\"presentation\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*urpfDN5v3xZ41XskIApfFA.png\" width=\"288\" height=\"448\" srcSet=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*urpfDN5v3xZ41XskIApfFA.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*urpfDN5v3xZ41XskIApfFA.png 288w\" sizes=\"288px\" role=\"presentation\"/></noscript></div></div></div></a></figure><p id=\"a08c\" class=\"hk hl dt hm b hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih dl eq\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/mindset-2\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">Mindset</strong></a> is a well-regarded psychology book that explores the power of one’s thinking. Dweck’s core theory is that is isn’t just our talent that makes us successful, but more importantly, whether we approach life with a fixed or growth mindset. With a fixed mindset, you believe failure means something is wrong with you. On the other hand, with a growth mindset, you see failure as an opportunity to grow and become better. The author guides us through various topics—from parenting and relationships, to school and business—and explains how developing a growth mindset in all areas of our lives can help us reach our full potential. This book gets a bit repetitive at some points, but it is most certainly worth the read.</p></div></div></section><div class=\"n p er ii ij ik\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in\"></span></div><section class=\"dl dm dn do dp\"><div class=\"n p\"><div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dq ai aj\"><figure class=\"gs gt gu gv gw gr cx cy paragraph-image\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/the-road-less-traveled\"><div class=\"cx cy ip\"><div class=\"hc s hd he\"><div class=\"ix hg s\"><div class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj bk ha hb\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj hh hi hj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/40/1*jmyBcuERz9jQvfhIQf_blg.png?q=20\" width=\"288\" height=\"442\" role=\"presentation\"/></div><img alt=\"\" class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj c\" width=\"288\" height=\"442\" role=\"presentation\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*jmyBcuERz9jQvfhIQf_blg.png\" width=\"288\" height=\"442\" srcSet=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*jmyBcuERz9jQvfhIQf_blg.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*jmyBcuERz9jQvfhIQf_blg.png 288w\" sizes=\"288px\" role=\"presentation\"/></noscript></div></div></div></a></figure><p id=\"e36b\" class=\"hk hl dt hm b hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih dl eq\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/the-road-less-traveled\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">The Road Less Traveled</strong></a> is a truly profound book. The author, M. Scott Peck, opens with the line, “Life is difficult.” This read is the ultimate roadmap to dealing with some of life’s greatest challenges with grace and love. Topics include: how to problem solve; dealing with pain; delaying gratification; being open to challenge; and developing a dedication to reality and personal growth. More than anything, these 315 pages will leave you feeling more in touch with the greatest truths in the universe—and how they can guide you to greater heights of self-understanding and love.</p></div></div></section><div class=\"n p er ii ij ik\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in\"></span></div><section class=\"dl dm dn do dp\"><div class=\"n p\"><div class=\"ab ac ae af ag dq ai aj\"><figure class=\"gs gt gu gv gw gr cx cy paragraph-image\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/the-school-of-greatness-2\"><div class=\"cx cy ip\"><div class=\"hc s hd he\"><div class=\"ix hg s\"><div class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj bk ha hb\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj hh hi hj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/40/1*W5hyzlXi4KB21ekkJnBoOA.png?q=20\" width=\"288\" height=\"442\" role=\"presentation\"/></div><img alt=\"\" class=\"gx gy t u v gz aj c\" width=\"288\" height=\"442\" role=\"presentation\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" class=\"t u v gz aj\" src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*W5hyzlXi4KB21ekkJnBoOA.png\" width=\"288\" height=\"442\" srcSet=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/552/1*W5hyzlXi4KB21ekkJnBoOA.png 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/576/1*W5hyzlXi4KB21ekkJnBoOA.png 288w\" sizes=\"288px\" role=\"presentation\"/></noscript></div></div></div></a></figure><p id=\"eadf\" class=\"hk hl dt hm b hn ho hp hq hr hs ht hu hv hw hx hy hz ia ib ic id ie if ig ih dl eq\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/books/the-school-of-greatness-2\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">The School of Greatness</strong></a> is an uplifting read by author Lewis Howes (who also hosts an awesome podcast by the same name, which you can check out <a href=\"http://lewishowes.com/category/podcast/\" class=\"ck ir\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong class=\"hm is\">here</strong></a>). Over the last several years, he’s interviewed hundreds of successful athletes, entrepreneurs, creatives, and thought leaders—from Tony Robbins to Elizabeth Gilbert to Larry King. In this book, he lays out his framework for personal development based on what he’s learned from all of those people that he calls his greatness “professors.” You’ll learn how to clarify your vision, master your body, build positive habits, and live a life of service. This is a great book that will help you find clarity and motivation around your biggest personal goals.</p></div></div></section><div class=\"n p er ii ij ik\" role=\"separator\"><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in io\"></span><span class=\"il ew gb im in\"></span></div><section class=\"dl dm dn do dp\"><div cla